1
00:00:11,166 --> 00:00:13,250
[SEIJI]
Is that true?

2
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:14,958
Those poor girls.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,541
[SEIJI shudders]

4
00:00:17,625 --> 00:00:21,333
So you're saying that SPR5
is fated to disappear,

5
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:22,458
just like that?

6
00:00:22,541 --> 00:00:24,916
[rattling in hall]

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,041
[gasps]

8
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:28,333
[footsteps departing]

9
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:29,875
♪

10
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,625
[YUA]
No way. We're being disbanded?

11
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:41,000
But why?

12
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,000
[line ringing]

13
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,916
[ringing continues, connects]

14
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,125
Yumiko. You all right?

15
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,583
[breathing shakily]

16
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:30,166
[weakly]
Yeah. You make it?

17
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:32,958
'Kay.

18
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,166
That's good.

19
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:37,208
For now, keep moving.

20
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,416
I'll call you again
once I find Kouta.

21
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,000
[line distorts]

22
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:43,750
[TAKUYA]
Got it. We'll meet up after.

23
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,250
By the way, we found Geek.

24
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,958
-Since we have a truck--
-[line disconnects]

25
00:02:50,583 --> 00:02:52,958
-[line ringing]
-[TAKUYA sighs]

26
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,291
[monitor beeping]

27
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:03,375
-[rapid beeping]
-[WOMAN screaming in pain]

28
00:03:03,458 --> 00:03:05,333
-[steady beeping]
-[screaming continues]

29
00:03:07,541 --> 00:03:08,791
[mechanical whirring]

30
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:12,458
[WOMAN gasping in pain]

31
00:03:12,541 --> 00:03:14,791
[high pitched whirring]

32
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,875
-[rapid beeping]
-[screaming continues]

33
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:27,083
[TAKUYA]
What's wrong? Have a bad dream?

34
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:29,291
[YUKI]
I'm fine.

35
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,416
It's just hard
to sleep back here.

36
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,708
[TAKUYA]
Try anyway.

37
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:35,000
Getting sleep'll help you
grow up strong.

38
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:38,541
Huh? Stop treating me
like I'm a child.

39
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:41,166
[TAKUYA scoffs]

40
00:03:47,958 --> 00:03:49,041
-[GEEK] Wait.
-[TAKUYA] Huh?

41
00:03:49,125 --> 00:03:50,250
[GEEK]
This is crazy.

42
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,333
It's just like I thought.

43
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:53,250
-Geek.
-Takuya.

44
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,291
-Oh, hey.
-Listen. Call me crazy,

45
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:56,791
but I feel like
we're going in circles.

46
00:03:56,875 --> 00:03:59,583
You see that sign?
It was for an SPR5 concert.

47
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:01,250
[TAKUYA]
Why don't you focus on driving?

48
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,750
[GEEK]
No, you don't get it.

49
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,375
SPR5's been
gone for years.

50
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:05,750
They were caught
in the Lost.

51
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,208
I didn't realize.

52
00:04:07,291 --> 00:04:08,708
[GEEK]
This is insane.

53
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:11,208
I don't know what's going on,
but it's not normal.

54
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:13,291
We might be
in a major bind here.

55
00:04:13,375 --> 00:04:14,708
Yeah, I see that.

56
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:17,875
[GEEK] What is this?
It doesn't make any sense.

57
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:22,500
What the hell, man?

58
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:24,833
No matter what I do,
we end up right back here.

59
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:27,750
[TAKUYA] We're able to move
some at least.

60
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,333
But we're restricted
to this general area.

61
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:33,666
[GEEK]
I think I remember this venue.

62
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:37,125
Pretty sure that SPR5 only ever
did a single concert here.

63
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,166
'Cause three months
after that,

64
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,833
they had a show
at the Martial Arts Hall

65
00:04:40,916 --> 00:04:42,166
and got caught in the Lost.

66
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:44,000
This doesn't make sense.

67
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:45,041
[GEEK]
Hmm?

68
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:51,208
[HOMURA]
Yua, come back.

69
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:52,375
[GEEK gasps]

70
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:57,125
-It's really them.
-[HOMURA] What's with you?

71
00:04:57,208 --> 00:04:58,500
[YUA] Look, I'm not
trying to get ahead

72
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:00,500
of anyone in the group,
I promise.

73
00:05:00,583 --> 00:05:02,708
I'm just saying that we need
to grow our fan base faster.

74
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:05,041
Hang on, is this about
the meet and greets?

75
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,708
That's already been decided.

76
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:08,416
We talked with Seiji
and agreed to stop.

77
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,875
-[RENA] Mm-hmm!
-But--

78
00:05:09,958 --> 00:05:12,583
We just need to focus
on performing at our best.

79
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,083
Forget the promotion stuff.

80
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:16,041
Seiji can handle
all that by himself.

81
00:05:16,125 --> 00:05:17,750
Speak up, Rena.

82
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:21,208
If you think things are fine
like this too, then say so.

83
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,291
Honestly,
I'm having enough trouble

84
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:24,833
just keeping my place
in the group.

85
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:26,791
The popularity polls
have been rough.

86
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:30,666
That's really SPR5.

87
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,041
Yua's standing right there,
just a few feet away.

88
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:37,875
Looks like they're having
a disagreement.

89
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:40,875
[YUA]
Why are you all so stupid?

90
00:05:40,958 --> 00:05:43,875
Do you want us to get disbanded?

91
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:45,458
[ALL gasp]

92
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:48,833
Where'd you get this idea from?
Seiji wouldn't do that.

93
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:51,708
Maybe you're just stressed
from the tour?

94
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:53,708
[YUA]
No. Why won't you listen to me?!

95
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:55,041
Just forget it.

96
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:56,291
Yua!

97
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,583
-[GEEK panting]
-Geek, stop.

98
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,458
I know that this bothers you,

99
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:03,833
but we need to focus
on getting out of here.

100
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:05,291
But we--

101
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:07,625
[TAKUYA] There are routes
we haven't tried yet.

102
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:09,625
[GEEK sighs]

103
00:06:09,708 --> 00:06:11,000
[GEEK]
All right, fine.

104
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,500
[YUMIKO shuddering]

105
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,250
[gasping in fear]

106
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,541
[YUMIKO]
Kouta?

107
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,000
[heavy breathing]

108
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:28,458
[flashlight clatters]

109
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:33,833
[line ringing]

110
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,666
[tires screech]

111
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,125
[ALL gasp]

112
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:47,875
[HOMURA]
What's with you?

113
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:49,250
[YUA] Look, I'm not
trying to get ahead

114
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,000
of anyone in the group,
I promise.

115
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:53,750
Sounds like the exact
same conversation.

116
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,875
We're not just stuck
in this place.

117
00:06:55,958 --> 00:06:58,375
We're stuck in
some weird time loop.

118
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:01,333
[YUA]
No. Why won't you listen to me?!

119
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,375
-Just forget it.
-[HOMURA] Yua!

120
00:07:03,458 --> 00:07:05,291
[grunting]

121
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:11,000
[tires screeching]

122
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:12,958
-[GEEK] Sorry!
-Hey, what're you doing?

123
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:15,625
Let him.
I wanna follow her too.

124
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:20,458
[GEEK]
Yua!

125
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:23,458
♪

126
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:29,791
[ALL panting]

127
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,250
[GEEK]
Found her!

128
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,291
[GEEK panting]

129
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,750
Um...

130
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,333
Hey, Yua.

131
00:07:50,916 --> 00:07:52,000
Listen.

132
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,041
The concert's starting soon.

133
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,458
If you don't hurry back,
you'll miss it.

134
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,083
[YUA] Sorry, you have
the wrong person.

135
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:01,083
[GEEK]
Huh?

136
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:04,791
Yeah. Could have told you
that would happen.

137
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:06,375
If I remember right,

138
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:08,708
SPR5 are celebrating
their first year together

139
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,041
with the current roster.

140
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:11,958
That's what this show's about.

141
00:08:12,041 --> 00:08:14,291
[YUKI]
Yeah, that's true.

142
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:16,500
It was an anniversary concert.

143
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:18,541
But Yua didn't go
for some reason.

144
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:20,166
[GEEK]
Oh, yeah.

145
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,708
There was an announcement
that she wasn't feeling well.

146
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:24,416
But it was pretty controversial.

147
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,541
A lot of fans didn't think
she was really sick.

148
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:29,416
[TAKUYA] Fascinating. Now can we
get back to our problems?

149
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:32,166
[GEEK] You don't get it.
There's more to it than that.

150
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,375
-[TAKUYA] Hmm?
-[YUKI gasps]

151
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:35,041
There's no doubt
that we're in the past.

152
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:37,083
-[inaudible]
-[GEEK] I'm not sure how.

153
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,666
My best guess is that
we entered a rip in space-time

154
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:42,250
because we got
too close to Lost.

155
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:45,125
If we change the past,
we'll change the future, too.

156
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:46,583
I have to do this!

157
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:47,833
[TAKUYA]
Wait.

158
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:51,000
If there's a way
to save them from the Lost,

159
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,791
then I'm gonna find it!

160
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:54,291
[TAKUYA]
Hmm.

161
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:56,500
If we are in the past,

162
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:59,500
that still doesn't explain
why this loop keeps repeating.

163
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,750
[TAKUYA] I'm worried about
Yumiko and Kouta.

164
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,083
Let's go back.

165
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:12,250
[HARUKA] Why has Yua
been acting so weird?

166
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,416
[NAMI] Don't know.
It's like a switch flipped.

167
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,708
[HOMURA]
What do we do?

168
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:17,708
She's so important to the show.

169
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,583
We can't perform without her.

170
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:21,958
Yeah, but it's too late
for us to cancel.

171
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,208
Oh, Yua, please come back.

172
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:25,833
-[door opens]
-[GIRLS gasp]

173
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:27,208
[HARUKA]
Huh?

174
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:28,583
Atsuko, you're here?

175
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:31,125
All of you, listen to me.

176
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:34,291
I have a message
for you from Seiji.

177
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:36,541
They're what?

178
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:39,083
But what about Yua's reputation?

179
00:09:39,166 --> 00:09:41,000
[SEIJI]
The doors are open.

180
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:42,416
The show must go on.

181
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,916
As for Yua,

182
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,083
we'll tell the public
that she got sick.

183
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:49,458
No way.

184
00:09:49,541 --> 00:09:50,750
[HARUKA sighs]

185
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:52,833
♪

186
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:56,791
[GEEK panting]

187
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,291
[GEEK]
I thought you might be here.

188
00:10:00,375 --> 00:10:02,041
-[YUA gasps]
-[GEEK grunting in effort]

189
00:10:02,125 --> 00:10:03,583
[YUA]
How'd you find me?

190
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:06,416
[GEEK] You mentioned this place
in your blog once.

191
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,916
You wrote that you liked
the ocean view.

192
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,208
I what?
I never wrote about that.

193
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:13,583
[GEEK]
But you will. Someday.

194
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:15,083
[gasps]

195
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:18,875
Look, uh, this might
sound crazy, but your show

196
00:10:18,958 --> 00:10:20,791
at the Martial Arts Hall
in three months,

197
00:10:20,875 --> 00:10:22,791
you need to make sure
that it gets canceled.

198
00:10:22,875 --> 00:10:25,291
[YUA]
Huh? And why would I do that?

199
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:28,250
[GEEK]
No use. Guess I should've known.

200
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:30,666
Come on. You can't give up yet.

201
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:31,875
There's still hope.

202
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,750
Just find a way to convince her.

203
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,041
[GEEK] Look, Yua,

204
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,166
I'm sorry to bring this up,

205
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,458
but I'm just worried about you

206
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:39,000
because you haven't been
doing well lately.

207
00:10:39,083 --> 00:10:40,625
I mean, you messed up
your choreography

208
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:42,375
for the very first time
the other day.

209
00:10:43,791 --> 00:10:46,375
I think maybe you need
to take a break.

210
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:48,916
And that it might be
a good time for it?

211
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:54,666
[TAKUYA] So you're saying
Yua's a Tama-shi?

212
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:55,958
[YUKI]
I'm not sure.

213
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:57,500
But that's what my gut tells me.

214
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:59,750
This strange pocket in time.

215
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:02,458
I feel like she might be
the one who created it.

216
00:11:02,541 --> 00:11:04,166
You have any reason
to think that?

217
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:08,541
These Tama-shi,
are they some kinda ghosts?

218
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:11,500
I guess they might've
been human once.

219
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:13,041
The ones
we've come across so far

220
00:11:13,125 --> 00:11:14,916
have acted like
mindless killers.

221
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,750
Could be that they were
being controlled.

222
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,875
Like you did with Akira?

223
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:23,750
So you might not be the only one
who can call Tama-shi?

224
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:26,000
I have no idea.

225
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:27,416
[TAKUYA]
Neither do I.

226
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,958
But on the plus side,

227
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:31,291
looks like you're figuring out
how your power works.

228
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:33,916
Just what did the Agency
do to you?

229
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:38,000
Sorry.

230
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:40,541
Damn it.

231
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:44,291
We're right back
where we started again.

232
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:47,083
[YUA] You're talking about
our last concert, right?

233
00:11:47,166 --> 00:11:48,708
I messed up pretty big there.

234
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:52,000
Tried to do a move
I hadn't really practiced.

235
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:54,166
[GEEK] It wasn't really
your fault though.

236
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,833
You took Rena's place
because she wasn't feeling well.

237
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,791
Right?

238
00:11:58,875 --> 00:12:00,208
[YUA]
You have good eyes.

239
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:01,500
I care, is all.

240
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:03,625
You know, other fans
misunderstand you,

241
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:05,166
but you're a kind person.

242
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,666
I've seen how hard you work.

243
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:09,250
[YUA] Come on, it's no
big secret that I'm devious.

244
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:10,916
That isn't you!

245
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,750
It's just a persona you use
to attract fans to the group.

246
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,458
[YUA]
He saw right through me.

247
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,541
I hope you know
that you don't have to act like

248
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,125
some kind of
rebellious bad girl.

249
00:12:20,208 --> 00:12:21,625
There's no need.

250
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:24,125
You could take the top spot
in the popularity polls

251
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:25,958
just by being yourself.

252
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,708
You don't have to sacrifice
who you are

253
00:12:27,791 --> 00:12:29,916
just to drive up interest
in the group.

254
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,958
You were doing enough
for SPR5 before all this, Yua.

255
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:35,333
You're an integral part of
the team just the way you are.

256
00:12:35,416 --> 00:12:37,041
You didn't hear
what I heard!

257
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:38,333
[GEEK]
Huh?

258
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:40,916
[YUA] I heard that we were
gonna disappear.

259
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:41,833
[GEEK] Huh?!

260
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:46,750
I know that it's true,
'cause Seiji said it.

261
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,750
SPR5 is fated to disappear.

262
00:12:51,583 --> 00:12:52,708
[gasps]

263
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:57,000
Yua? Yua!

264
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:05,500
-[YUKI] Hey.
-[TAKUYA] Hmm?

265
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:07,833
If you could revisit
your own past,

266
00:13:07,916 --> 00:13:10,625
is there anything
you would try to change?

267
00:13:10,708 --> 00:13:12,625
[TAKUYA]
Not sure why you're asking.

268
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:15,666
But I think most people
would probably say yes.

269
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,041
We all have regrets.

270
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:19,500
[YUKI gasps]

271
00:13:19,583 --> 00:13:20,875
[tires screech]

272
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:22,208
No use.

273
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,166
No matter where we go,
we end up back here.

274
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:26,833
[YUA]
Why are you all so stupid?

275
00:13:26,916 --> 00:13:28,333
Do you want us...

276
00:13:28,416 --> 00:13:31,083
[YUKI] Why do we always end up
back in this moment?

277
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:33,583
[TAKUYA] It's frustrating
hearin' these kids.

278
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,875
Huh?
And why is that?

279
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:39,625
Because she obviously isn't
telling them everything.

280
00:13:41,541 --> 00:13:44,583
So, then, maybe that's why.

281
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:46,333
Because she couldn't be honest.

282
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:48,750
-[GEEK] Takuya!
-[TAKUYA] Geek?

283
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:49,958
[GEEK panting]

284
00:13:50,041 --> 00:13:51,375
[GEEK]
I talked to Yua.

285
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:56,041
So SPR5 is
"fated to disappear?"

286
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:58,583
That's what she heard
the producer say.

287
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:01,666
And it explains why
she's acting so distraught.

288
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:03,291
It's his call.

289
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:05,916
So if he really planned
to disband the group,

290
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,250
why wouldn't he just
tell them as much?

291
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:09,625
[GEEK]
I'm not sure.

292
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:13,000
[TAKUYA] That phrasing.
"Fated to disappear."

293
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:14,250
No way.

294
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:16,333
What's this producer's name?

295
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:18,000
I'm pretty sure it was Seiji.

296
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:21,083
He's in the concert hall, right?
I'm gonna go talk to him.

297
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:23,083
Hey, Takuya,
hold on a minute, will ya?

298
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:25,041
We don't even know
what the guy looks like!

299
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:27,416
Hey, um, Geek?

300
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,458
[GEEK]
Huh?

301
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:30,208
[YUKI]
Will you take me to Yua?

302
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:33,958
[footsteps approaching]

303
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:38,000
You won't change anything
by sitting in place.

304
00:14:39,875 --> 00:14:41,375
-What?
-Come on.

305
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,416
[YUA]
Who are you?

306
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,916
Hold on.

307
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,333
Wait.

308
00:14:46,416 --> 00:14:49,125
[YUKI]
Stay here and you'll regret it.

309
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:51,708
[YUA gasps]

310
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:54,125
[YUKI] You don't want
to live with regret.

311
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:55,500
Take it from me.

312
00:15:00,875 --> 00:15:02,750
[YUA]
Stop, I can't keep up.

313
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,625
[YUKI] You were on
the track team, weren't you?

314
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:05,958
So run.

315
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:07,416
[YUKI]
Back then,

316
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:10,125
I didn't have
the courage to act.

317
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:13,333
I was experimented on.
Day after day.

318
00:15:13,416 --> 00:15:15,166
But I never tried to run.

319
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:17,125
I was convinced
that it was pointless.

320
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,625
[YUA]
No, I won't do it!

321
00:15:19,708 --> 00:15:20,541
[YUKI sighs]

322
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:24,000
[YUKI]
You have to go.

323
00:15:24,083 --> 00:15:25,291
Or else you'll regret it.

324
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,375
That's just how it is.

325
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:30,666
So I have to take you.

326
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,333
Or else I'll regret it.

327
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:34,916
[YUA] Hmm.

328
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,375
[BOTH panting]

329
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,416
[indistinct chatter]

330
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:46,083
[TAKUYA] Shit. Where is this
friggin' producer hiding?

331
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:51,708
[YUA]
I'm sorry, but I can't go back.

332
00:15:51,791 --> 00:15:54,291
I said such terrible things.

333
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:57,375
I was only trying
to save the group,

334
00:15:57,458 --> 00:15:59,666
but everything just backfired.

335
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,333
There's no place
for me with them.

336
00:16:01,416 --> 00:16:02,708
Not anymore.

337
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:06,250
[YUKI inhales sharply]

338
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,625
[YUKI]
You don't know that.

339
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:10,416
[YUA] Huh.

340
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,333
Huh?

341
00:16:11,416 --> 00:16:12,833
[ALL]
Yua.

342
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:15,666
We thought we heard
your voice back here.

343
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:17,791
You had us worried,
you know that?

344
00:16:17,875 --> 00:16:18,875
[YUA crying]
Sorry.

345
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,833
I'm so sorry. I just...

346
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:25,583
It's okay.
Let's talk this over later.

347
00:16:25,666 --> 00:16:27,833
First things first,
we have a show to put on.

348
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:30,000
Yeah. We'll need
all our members.

349
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:32,458
Right.

350
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,458
[footsteps running]

351
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:36,208
[GIRLS chuckling]

352
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,250
Um...

353
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:41,166
[YUKI chuckles softly]

354
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,750
Thanks for the help.

355
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:45,208
[GEEK crying]

356
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:47,833
[GEEK] Talk about
an emotional roller coaster.

357
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,458
[YUA panting]

358
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:52,750
I overheard you two earlier
and you really surprised me.

359
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:55,666
How did you know that Yua
was part of a track team?

360
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,500
That's some pretty
obscure trivia,

361
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,458
even for a crazed fan like me.

362
00:16:59,541 --> 00:17:02,250
Read it online.
I was a fan myself.

363
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,833
[GEEK]
Wait, I'm not alone?

364
00:17:04,916 --> 00:17:07,000
I've met another Yua fan?!

365
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:09,458
I think Yua should
sound us off today.

366
00:17:09,541 --> 00:17:10,416
[NAMI]
Yeah, agreed.

367
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,708
Huh?

368
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:14,708
[chuckles softly]

369
00:17:14,791 --> 00:17:16,041
Right, let's have a great show.

370
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:17,833
The fans are waiting for us.

371
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:20,583
[ALL] Time to show them
how the Supreme Five do it!

372
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:24,958
Aw, man!

373
00:17:25,041 --> 00:17:28,000
All that work and we don't even
get to see the show!

374
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:30,083
-[rumbling]
-[TAKUYA gasps]

375
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:33,791
[YUKI]
The sky.

376
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,958
[GEEK] Think that means
we left the rip in time?

377
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:42,458
[TAKUYA]
So it would seem.

378
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:46,583
[sobbing]

379
00:17:46,666 --> 00:17:48,500
-Wait.
-[tires screech]

380
00:17:48,583 --> 00:17:50,750
I've gotta check and see
if that was really the past.

381
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,208
Just one way to be sure.

382
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:55,625
[GEEK] Huh?

383
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:01,666
I don't get it.
Nothing changed.

384
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,625
Yua missed her appearance
at that concert,

385
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:07,375
and SPR5 was still
caught up in the Lost.

386
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:08,708
No way.

387
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,958
Then what was
the point of all that?

388
00:18:12,041 --> 00:18:13,625
What did we just go through?

389
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:16,625
Sorry. You should j-j...

390
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:18,750
You should just go on ahead.

391
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:19,916
[TAKUYA]
Got it.

392
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:23,625
[TAKUYA]
If that wasn't the past,

393
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:25,125
then what the hell was it?

394
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:27,375
Feels like we know less now
than we did before.

395
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:31,458
Actually, thanks to this,
I think I understand now.

396
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,166
-I get what the Tama-shi are.
-[TAKUYA] Hmm?

397
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:39,125
That day countless people
with love, hope, and regret

398
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:41,166
were suddenly torn
from this world.

399
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:44,208
They never got to tell
their crushes how they felt.

400
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,125
Or accomplish their dreams.

401
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:48,208
Or say goodbye
to their families.

402
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:51,833
I think that a Tama-shi is
the unfinished will of a person

403
00:18:51,916 --> 00:18:54,291
caught in the Lost, given form.

404
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:57,666
The last thing Akira did
was try to protect me.

405
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:59,791
Okay, then what about Yua?

406
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:02,708
Even months later, she must
have been full of regret.

407
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:05,500
I think the place
we found ourselves trapped in

408
00:19:05,583 --> 00:19:07,875
was a world
that her Tama-shi created.

409
00:19:07,958 --> 00:19:09,750
[TAKUYA]
Damn. Tough break.

410
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,625
[YUKI]
We couldn't change the past.

411
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:15,000
But I don't think
it was pointless.

412
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,708
[HOMURA] This next song
was the very first one

413
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:24,458
that we performed
with all our current members.

414
00:19:24,541 --> 00:19:25,750
No matter what lies ahead,

415
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:28,083
the five of us
will overcome it together.

416
00:19:28,166 --> 00:19:31,791
This song's theme is our will
to keep that promise.

417
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:34,875
I tend to drag the group down,
so that works out for me.

418
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:37,000
Clumsiness is part
of your character.

419
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:38,750
I'm not a character,
I'm a person.

420
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:41,208
Oh! So what does
my character do?

421
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,166
-Cause trouble.
-Say what?

422
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:45,375
We know we're
a little bit different.

423
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:47,083
So we wanted to say...

424
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:50,458
[ALL] We're grateful
for your support! Thanks!

425
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:52,916
Now please enjoy our next song.

426
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,250
[ALL]
"With Your Breath."

427
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:55,958
[AUDIENCE cheering]

428
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:58,791
♪

429
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:33,541
[high-pitched static]

430
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:34,666
[YUKI groans]

431
00:21:35,958 --> 00:21:37,333
What's wrong?

432
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:38,500
[YUKI groans]

433
00:21:38,583 --> 00:21:39,916
[YUKI]
Something's nearby.

434
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,291
[TAKUYA]
A Tama-shi?

435
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:45,083
Leave it to me.

436
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:48,291
If you buy some time, then I can
find out what it's thinking.

437
00:21:48,375 --> 00:21:50,416
Speak to me.

438
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,875
State your will.

439
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:57,500
[TAKUYA gasps]

440
00:21:58,875 --> 00:22:00,625
-[TAKUYA grunts]
-[YUKI screams]

441
00:22:02,375 --> 00:22:03,833
[groans]

442
00:22:03,916 --> 00:22:07,458
♪

443
00:22:07,541 --> 00:22:08,750
[YUKI]
Takuya!

444
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,625
[SOUMA]
My "will?"

445
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:13,625
Gee, sis.
What are you going on about?

446
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:15,625
[YUKI]
Souma?

447
00:22:16,708 --> 00:22:17,625
[TAKUYA groans]

448
00:22:17,708 --> 00:22:19,458
[SOUMA]
Been a while, Yuki.

449
00:22:19,541 --> 00:22:21,708
I missed you.

450
00:22:21,791 --> 00:22:23,750
Hold on.

451
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,375
What did you do?

452
00:22:25,458 --> 00:22:26,666
[SOUMA]
What did I do?

453
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:28,041
Same thing you did.

454
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:30,958
Come on, let's go home.

455
00:22:31,041 --> 00:22:32,875
[gasps]

456
00:22:32,958 --> 00:22:36,041
[SOUMA] What's the matter?
You just found out I'm alive.

457
00:22:36,125 --> 00:22:37,458
Aren't you glad?

458
00:22:37,541 --> 00:22:39,375
[YUKI] Stop this.

459
00:22:39,458 --> 00:22:40,416
[SOUMA]
Huh?

460
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:42,000
[YUKI]
Open your eyes, Souma!

461
00:22:42,083 --> 00:22:43,458
My eyes are wide open,

462
00:22:43,541 --> 00:22:45,750
you're the one
who's having trouble seeing.

463
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,000
I get it.

464
00:22:47,083 --> 00:22:49,250
He's the problem.

465
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:50,750
Not for long.

466
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,458
[TAKUYA groaning sharply]

467
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,666
Takuya!

468
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,583
[gasps] Stop this,
you're gonna kill him!

469
00:22:57,666 --> 00:23:00,291
[SOUMA] You should come with me,
I mean it.

470
00:23:00,375 --> 00:23:02,500
After all,
the two of us are family.

471
00:23:03,583 --> 00:23:05,291
And seeing as
our dad is gone,

472
00:23:05,375 --> 00:23:07,083
we really need to
support each other.

473
00:23:07,166 --> 00:23:08,708
-[TAKUYA groaning]
-[bones cracking]

474
00:23:09,708 --> 00:23:13,666
Please just let him go!

475
00:23:17,458 --> 00:23:18,708
[explosion]

476
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:20,916
[gasps]

477
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,041
[wind whistling]

478
00:23:24,541 --> 00:23:26,958
-[rumbling]
-What the hell's going on here?

479
00:23:27,041 --> 00:23:28,000
These waves.

480
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:37,875
♪

481
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,041
[inaudible]

482
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,375
[TAKUYA]
Next Episode, "Suspicion."

